g%20power%20grabs%20for%20Damascus.%20Russian%20military%20bases%20remain%20firmly%20planted%20along%20the%20coast%2C%20Israeli%20forces%20patrol%20the%20southern%20fringes%2C%20US%20troops%20stick%20to%20their%20northeast%20corner%20and%20Turkey%20remains%20a%20strong%20influence%20and%20a%20key%20player.%20Not%20to%20be%20outdone%2C%20Iran%20is%20busy%20trying%20to%20rebuild%20its%20covert%20web%20of%20influence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%2C%20I%20am%20afraid%2C%20could%20possibly%20be%20Syria's%20worst-case%20scenario%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20and%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Game%20Of%20Chess%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%202024%20draws%20to%20a%20close%2C%20a%20year%20that%20has%20been%20nothing%20short%20of%20seismic%20for%20West%20Asia%2C%20Syria%20stands%20at%20a%20crossroads%E2%80%94a%20precarious%2C%20nail-biting%20threshold%20where%20the%20future%20is%20frustratingly%20unpredictable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20collapse%20of%20the%20Assad%20dynasty's%2054-year%20authoritarian%20rule%20has%20sparked%20a%20glimmer%20of%20hope%20for%20millions%20of%20long-suffering%20Syrians.%20But%20it's%20also%20thrown%20them%20headfirst%20into%20uncharted%20waters.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnIf%20you%20look%20closely%2C%20Syria%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20giant%20geopolitical%20chessboard%2C%20with%20too%20many%20players%20hovering%20over%20the%20pieces%2C%20waiting%20to%20see%20who%20dares%20make%20the%20first%20move.%20For%20now%2C%20it's%20all%20guesswork%20and%20a%20high-stakes%20game%20of%20wait-and-watch.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnBut%20amid%20Syria's%20turmoil%2C%20HTS%2C%20once%20the%20al-Nusra%20Front%2C%20has%20swapped%20its%20militant%20garb%20for%20Western-style%20suits%20as%20its%20leader%2C%20Abu%20al-Jolani%E2%80%94who%20now%20prefers%20to%20call%20himself%20by%20his%20real%20name%20Ahmed%20al-Sharaa%E2%80%94attempts%20a%20political%20makeover.%20Western%20powers%2C%20while%20still%20labelling%20HTS%20a%20terrorist%20group%2C%20are%20taking%20a%20wait%20and%20see%20approach.%20They%20have%20laid%20down%20the%20terms%3A%20protect%20minorities%2C%20ensure%20a%20peaceful%20transition%20and%20maybe%20earn%20relief%20from%20sanctions.%20But%20skepticism%20lingers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETurkey%20continues%20its%20game%20of%20geopolitical%20chess%2C%20backing%20the%20Syrian%20National%20Army%20(SNA)%20against%20the%20Syrian%20Democratic%20Forces%20(SDF)%2C%20which%20it%20accuses%20of%20being%20a%20PKK%20front.%20Ankara%20insists%20the%20PKK%2C%20a%20long-time%20thorn%20in%20its%20side%2C%20be%20disarmed.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20US%20and%20UK%20champion%20the%20SDF%20cause%20for%20its%20role%20in%20thrashing%20the%20Islamic%20State%20terrorists.%20--%20while%20all%20the%20while%20trying%20to%20mollify%20Turkey's%20security%20concerns.%20HTS%2C%20for%20its%20part%2C%20plays%20the%20diplomat%2C%20subtly%20supporting%20%E2%80%9Cfreedom%E2%80%9D%20for%20SDF%20areas%20while%20trying%20to%20keep%20the%20PKK%20card%20out%20of%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fall%20of%20Assad%20is%20a%20hard%20punch%20to%20Iran's%20%E2%80%9Caxis%20of%20resistance%2C%E2%80%9D%20slicing%20through%20its%20supply%20line%20to%20Hezbollah%20in%20Lebanon%20and%20unravelling%20a%20carefully%20knit%20network%20of%20proxies.%20Israel%2C%20never%20one%20to%20miss%20an%20opportunity%2C%20has%20stepped%20up%20its%20airstrikes%E2%80%94nearly%20500%20so%20far%E2%80%94on%20Syrian%20targets%20while%20expressing%20its%20intention%20to%20expand%20settlements%20in%20the%20Golan%20Heights.%20If%20anyone%20thought%20Assad's%20departure%20would%20calm%20the%20waters%2C%20Israel's%20actions%20suggest%20otherwise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20the%20Islamic%20State%2C%20rumours%20of%20its%20demise%20were%20premature.%20The%20Americans%2C%20who%20once%20boasted%20of%20defeating%20it%20forever%2C%20now%20acknowledge%20that%20the%20group%20is%20making%20a%20comeback%2C%20with%20attacks%20in%20Syria%20doubling%20in%202024.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%2C%20with%20its%20900%20boots%20on%20Syrian%20ground%2C%20is%20keeping%20a%20wary%20eye%20while%20managing%20detention%20camps%20teeming%20with%20Islamic%20State%20fighters%20and%20their%20families%E2%80%94a%20breeding%20ground%20for%20trouble.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council's%202015%20resolution%20to%20work%20on%20a%20new%20Syrian%20constitution%20and%20elections%20remains%20unfinished%20business.%20So%2C%20watch%20out%2C%20as%20in%20this%20theatre%20of%20chaos%2C%20the%20script%20is%20still%20being%20written%E2%80%94an%20act%20that%20will%20continue%20even%20after%20we%20enter%202025%E2%80%94with%20far%20too%20many%20authors%20vying%20to%20write%20its%20final%20chapter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHigh-Stakes%20Drama%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWest%20Asia%20has%20long%20been%20synonymous%20with%20power%20plays%2C%20ideological%20tussles%20and%20resource-driven%20strategies.%20The%20region%20remains%20a%20playground%20for%20US%20military%20might%2C%20still%20calling%20the%20shots.%20In%202024%2C%20brinkmanship%20hit%20new%20heights%2C%20with%20the%20Israel-Iran%20face-off%20narrowly%20avoiding%20a%20full-scale%20regional%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20year%20also%20witnessed%20relentless%20violence%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%2C%20with%20Hezbollah%20adding%20fuel%20to%20the%20fire.%20Over%2045%2C000%20Palestinians%20have%20been%20killed%2C%20and%20nearly%2090%25%20of%20Gaza's%20population%20has%20been%20left%20homeless.%20On%20November%2021%2C%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20(ICC)%20issued%20arrest%20warrants%20for%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20and%20former%20defence%20minister%20Yoav%20Gallant%2C%20accusing%20them%20of%20war%20crimes%20during%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%E2%80%94an%20unprecedented%20move%20against%20the%20leader%20of%20a%20major%20Western%20ally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20analysts%20believe%20Prime%20Minister%20Netanyahu's%20expansionist%20policies%20and%20hardline%20stance%20have%20sparked%20global%20outrage%2C%20yet%20Arab%20support%20for%20Palestine%20remains%20inconsistent%2C%20limited%20to%20fiery%20rhetoric%20rather%20than%20meaningful%20action.%20The%20conflict%20continues%20to%20derail%20efforts%20to%20normalise%20relations%20between%20Israel%20and%20Arab%20states%2C%20particularly%20Saudi%20Arabia%20under%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20which%20was%20initiated%20by%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20his%20first%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFragile%20Peace%2C%20Lingering%20Rivalries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20much-lauded%202023%20China-brokered%20rapprochement%20between%20arch-rivals%20Iran%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%20is%20already%20showing%20cracks.%20In%202024%2C%20their%20simmering%20rivalries%20have%20resurfaced%2C%20with%20Syria%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20dispute.%20Iran%20is%20pressuring%20Syria's%20interim%20government%20to%20honour%20a%20reported%20%2430%20billion%20bilateral%20assistance%20deal%E2%80%94not%20so%20much%20for%20the%20cash%2C%20but%20to%20keep%20its%20foothold%20in%20a%20post-Assad%20Syria.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia's%20attention%20remains%20divided%20between%20Yemen's%20quagmire%20and%20its%20'Vision%202030'%20ambitions.%20This%20fragile%20peace%20risks%20unravelling%20under%20unresolved%20tensions.%20Proxy%20conflicts%20in%20Yemen%20and%20Iraq%20could%20continue%20to%20simmer%20or%20boil%20over%2C%20potentially%20reigniting%20destabilising%20confrontations%20or%20paving%20the%20way%20for%20genuine%20regional%20integration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%20Retreat%20And%20Regional%20Power%20Shifts%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20Western%20analysts%20believe%20that%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20pivot%20to%20checkmating%20China%20has%20left%20West%20Asia%20playing%20a%20game%20of%20geopolitical%20musical%20chairs.%20Turkey%20is%20flexing%20its%20muscles%20as%20a%20mediator%20and%20powerbroker%2C%20while%20the%20UAE%20expands%20its%20influence%20through%20savvy%20economic%20deals%20and%20security%20initiatives.%20Russia%2C%20despite%20internal%20struggles%2C%20clings%20on%20to%20its%20strategic%20edge%20with%20military%20bases%20in%20Syria.%20A%20diminished%20US%20presence%20creates%20opportunities%20for%20regional%20powers%20to%20step%20up%20but%20also%20risks%20heightening%20competition.%20As%20Turkey%2C%20Iran%20and%20Saudi%20Arabia%20vie%20for%20dominance%2C%20West%20Asia's%20future%20looks%20more%20unpredictable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBeyond%20Oil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOPEC%20production%20cuts%20in%202024%20reinforced%20the%20region's%20dependence%20on%20crude%2C%20even%20as%20some%20member%20nations%20look%20to%20diversify.%20Saudi%20Arabia's%20NEOM%20megacity%20and%20green%20energy%20projects%20symbolise%20ambitions%20for%20a%20post-oil%20future.%20Success%20in%20diversification%20could%20stabilise%20the%20region%2C%20but%20failure%20would%20leave%20many%20nations%20vulnerable%20to%20socio-economic%20upheaval%20in%20a%20world%20moving%20beyond%20oil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Powerbroker%20In%20Waiting%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETurkey%20seems%20to%20be%20in%20pole%20position%20to%20spearhead%20Syria's%20reconstruction%20and%20play%20a%20significant%20role%20in%20stabilising%20West%20Asia.%20With%20its%20embassy%20in%20Damascus%20reopening%20after%2012%20years%2C%20Ankara%20is%20signalling%20its%20intent%20to%20play%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20Syria's%20recovery%20from%20civil%20war%20and%20economic%20devastation.%20In%20the%20long%20run%2C%20Turkey's%20influence%20is%20likely%20to%20grow%20as%20it%20navigates%20this%20complex%20rebuilding%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Turkey%20and%20the%20European%20Union%2C%20the%20stakes%20are%20high.%20The%20promise%20of%20a%20stable%20Syria%20isn't%20just%20about%20altruism%3B%20it's%20a%20strategic%20necessity.%20During%20her%20visit%20to%20Ankara%20on%20December%2017%2C%20European%20Commission%20President%20Ursula%20von%20der%20Leyen%20announced%20an%20additional%20%241%20billion%20in%20funding%20to%20Turkey%20for%20refugee%20support%E2%80%94a%20timely%20acknowledgement%20of%20Turkey's%20heavy%20lifting.%20Hosting%20around%203.5%20million%20Syrian%20refugees%2C%20Turkey%20has%20shouldered%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20crisis%2C%20while%20the%20EU%20has%20absorbed%20over%201.5%20million%20refugees%20since%20the%20conflict%20began%20in%202011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Turkey%20can%20balance%20its%20role%20as%20both%20a%20regional%20power%20and%20a%20bridge%20to%20the%20West%2C%20it%20could%20turn%20this%20moment%20into%20a%20diplomatic%20and%20humanitarian%20win.%20This%20will%20also%20have%20a%20stabilising%20influence%20in%20the%20entire%20West%20Asian%20countries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrump%20Factor%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWest%20Asia%20in%202024%20stands%20at%20a%20crossroads.%20While%20the%20region%20faces%20numerous%20challenges%E2%80%94from%20political%20instability%20to%20economic%20dependence%20on%20oil%20%E2%80%94there%20are%20also%20opportunities%20for%20transformation.%20Whether%202025%20becomes%20a%20year%20of%20renewal%20or%20regression%20depends%20on%20the%20choices%20made%20by%20regional%20and%20global%20actors%20alike.%20The%20Trump%20factor%20is%20going%20to%20have%20a%20significant%20say%20in%20how%20the%20new%20year%20and%20beyond%20will%20pan%20out%20for%20West%20Asia.%20So%20far%2C%20very%20mixed%20signals%20have%20come%20from%20the%20incoming%20Trump%20administration%20about%20the%20extent%20of%20its%20plans%20to%20be%20actively%20involved%20in%20the%20region.%20Until%20that%20is%20clear%20I%20believe%20no%20regional%20player%20will%20be%20willing%20to%20take%20any%20decisive%20step%20just%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20the%20curtain%20falls%20on%202024%2C%20one%20thing%20is%20clear%2C%20West%20Asia%20will%20remain%20a%20region%20whose%20dynamics%20will%20continue%20to%20shape%20the%20world%20for%20ye