an%20anything%20helpful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20I%20still%20noticed%20when%20my%20kids%20became%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkid-screen-addiction-child-psychologist-parent-tips-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edysregulated%20after%20certain%20types%20of%20screen%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20I%20didn't%20want%20that%20for%20them%20or%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20household.%20Rather%20than%20trying%20to%20figure%20it%20out%20on%20my%20own%2C%20I%20brought%20our%20kids%20into%20the%20conversation.%20What%20they%20brought%20up%20was%20eye-opening%20and%20really%20helpful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224e628a75-a350-4740-a546-cb8ba65c1df4%5C%22%3EScreens%20weren't%20a%20problem%20for%20just%20the%20kids%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20things%20the%20kids%20mentioned%20was%20that%20their%20father%20and%20I%20were%20also%20often%20on%20our%20screens%2C%20specifically%20our%20phones.%20They%20were%20confused%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20essentially%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbroke-parenting-rules-allowed-unlimited-screen-time-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eno%20rules%20around%20our%20screen%20use%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20they%20were%20also%20frustrated%20that%20sometimes%20they%20wanted%20our%20full%20attention%20but%20couldn't%20get%20it.%20This%20shifted%20my%20perspective%20and%20I%20realized%20that%20our%20conversation%20couldn't%20be%20just%20about%20their%20screens%20but%20had%20to%20be%20about%20the%20whole%20family's%20habits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20partner%20and%20I%20often%20used%20our%20phones%20for%20things%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-using-slack-at-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanswering%20Slack%20messages%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20texting%20people%20about%20all%20the%20life%20things%20that%20come%20up%2C%20but%20that%20wasn't%20clear%20to%20our%20kids.%20And%20it%20honestly%20didn't%20make%20a%20difference%20to%20them.%20They%20wanted%20undivided%20attention%20at%20certain%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20also%20refreshingly%20honest%20about%20how%20they%20felt%20after%20different%20screen%20time%20uses%20%E2%80%94%20the%20good%2C%20the%20bad%2C%20and%20the%20unknown.%20Most%20surprising%2C%20perhaps%2C%20was%20that%20they%20were%20very%20open%20to%20hearing%20our%20advice%20on%20how%20to%20handle%20screen%20time%20better%2C%20and%20they%20brought%20some%20great%20solutions%20to%20the%20table.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2287fe7f86-a67a-4619-9514-b69d620409f9%5C%22%3EI%20changed%20my%20screen%20time%20rules%2C%20and%20it%20wasn't%20easy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20most%20interesting%20aspects%20of%20this%20conversation%20was%20that%20we%20all%20proposed%20our%20own%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fkids-no-screens-home-weird-regrets-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escreen%20time%20rules%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20kids%20each%20came%20up%20with%20a%20thoughtful%20plan%20that%20my%20spouse%20and%20I%20approved%20after%20all%20the%20details%20were%20worked%20out%2C%20and%20I%20also%20created%20rules%20for%20myself.%20These%20included%20putting%20my%20phone%20away%20on%20our%20charging%20station%20between%205%20p.m.%20and%208%20p.m.%2C%20not%20wearing%20my%20Apple%20Watch%20when%20we%20were%20all%20together%2C%20and%20setting%20Apple's%20app%20limits%20on%20ones%20that%20were%20a%20time-suck%20(looking%20at%20you%2C%20Instagram).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20silly%20(did%20you%20really%20stand%20all%20day%20if%20Apple%20Watch%20doesn't%20say%20you%20did%3F)%20to%20the%20practical%20(sometimes%20I%20miss%20messages%20from%20people%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20answered%20sooner)%2C%20it%20was%20challenging%20at%20first.%20But%20ultimately%20I%20got%20used%20to%20this%20new%20habit%2C%20and%20it%20was%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224ce11f87-bb8d-4a88-a052-3ae63f949d80%5C%22%3EOu